			<a href="http://werblog.com/2011/07/the-potential-for-wireless-breakthroughs/#comment-397" class="social-posted-when" target="_blank">July 29, 2011</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="social-comment-body">
				<p>I read the white paper and I didn&#8217;t see that it supplies enough information to evaluate if this is new or mainly a reinvention or variant of multiuser MIMO. But he does provide enough information to call into question his claim that he can deliver only 2 ms latency, using that centralized signal processor. Plus, so far I also don&#8217;t see any technical reason why the signal processing has to be so centralized. Could distribute major pieces of the job to the dot coms, seemed to me. Seems to be a business method.</p>
